RALPH:
Yeah.

11:44.357 --> 11:45.990
You've got more in
common with the clown,

11:45.992 --> 11:47.141
except his suit's
more expensive.

11:47.143 --> 11:48.142
Hey, yo!

11:48.144 --> 11:49.160
(horn honks)

11:49.162 --> 11:50.311
I mean, what kind of loser

11:50.313 --> 11:52.413
has his bachelor party
ten yards from A.C.

11:52.415 --> 11:54.115
and doesn't even gamble?

11:59.588 --> 12:01.155
(tires screeching)

12:01.157 --> 12:02.990
(screams)
Oh. Oh, sorry.

12:02.992 --> 12:05.710
Sorry. Sorry.

12:05.712 --> 12:07.545
(chuckles)
Sorry.

12:07.547 --> 12:08.930
Oh... oh, wait.

12:08.932 --> 12:09.931
Just a little more.

12:09.933 --> 12:11.349
Okay, sorry.

12:11.351 --> 12:12.633
(sighs):
Okay.

12:12.635 --> 12:15.036
(speaking Chinese)

12:15.038 --> 12:18.439
...bro mitzvah!
(laughs)

12:18.441 --> 12:20.524
NARRATOR: <i>Kids, I'll skip over</i>
<i>the gambling.</i>

12:20.526 --> 12:22.893
<i>Like I said, it was</i>
<i>a complicated game.</i>

12:22.895 --> 12:25.446
<i>Although your old man</i>
<i>did pick it up pretty quickly.</i>

12:25.448 --> 12:27.565
(crowd cheers)

12:27.567 --> 12:28.532
Hey!

12:28.534 --> 12:30.568
You just won 300 bucks!

12:30.570 --> 12:32.937
I just lost $5,000.

12:32.939 --> 12:34.438
Oh, right.
'Cause the chicken.

12:34.440 --> 12:36.690
Yep, that-that's
$5,000, yeah.

12:36.692 --> 12:38.659
(laughs)

12:38.661 --> 12:39.794
See, I'm laughing

12:39.796 --> 12:41.662
because you couldn't see me
take my top off,

12:41.664 --> 12:43.998
but I just saw you lose your shirt.
Hey-yo!

12:44.000 --> 12:45.683
(horn honks)
We have to go back.

12:45.685 --> 12:47.885
(sneezes): Loser!
Sorry, that was a real sneeze.

12:47.887 --> 12:50.388
Might have made you miss
what I was saying.

12:50.390 --> 12:51.422
Loser!

12:51.424 --> 12:53.040
(laughs):
Loser.

12:53.042 --> 12:54.708
We're not going anywhere.

12:54.710 --> 12:57.878
I can still make
this night legendary.

12:57.880 --> 12:59.897
Uh, uh... (speaks Chinese)

12:59.899 --> 13:01.983
(replies in Chinese)

13:01.985 --> 13:03.717
Oh, oh.

13:03.719 --> 13:06.354
Okay, I got some credit.

13:06.356 --> 13:08.222
I just... mm...

13:08.224 --> 13:09.774
Marshall, stand over there
for good luck?

13:09.776 --> 13:11.309
Oh, sure.

13:15.947 --> 13:17.731
Okay, okay.

13:17.733 --> 13:20.251
(crowd chants in Chinese)

13:20.253 --> 13:21.669
(speaks Chinese)

13:22.838 --> 13:24.672
(crowd cheers)

13:24.674 --> 13:27.408
(laughs):
Oh! Oh!

13:27.410 --> 13:30.378
You crazy son of a bitch,
you did it!

13:30.380 --> 13:33.097
I just lost $80,000.

13:33.099 --> 13:34.849
Oh, right, right, yeah.
'Cause the black jelly bean.

13:34.851 --> 13:36.183
That-That's $80,000.
He's right.

13:36.185 --> 13:37.968
(clears throat)

13:37.970 --> 13:40.438
You know, Ralph,

13:40.440 --> 13:44.425
earlier at the salon, I
waxed on, then waxed off.

13:44.427 --> 13:46.260
(whispers):
Everywhere.

13:46.262 --> 13:49.363
Uh, listen, lady,
your husband is, like...

13:49.365 --> 13:51.649
Hey, where <i>is</i>
your husband?

13:51.651 --> 13:52.783
Marshall?

13:52.785 --> 13:54.068
Where's Marshall?!

13:54.070 --> 13:57.872
Okay, Lily,
don't overreact, but...

14:01.376 --> 14:02.576
Oh, oh.

14:02.578 --> 14:04.795
Okay, I got some credit.

14:04.797 --> 14:06.914
Marshall, stand over there
for good luck?

14:06.916 --> 14:09.083
Oh, sure.

14:12.787 --> 14:14.839
You sold my husband?!

14:14.841 --> 14:16.891
Lily, can you be more like
the Chinese mobster

14:16.893 --> 14:18.292
and give me some credit?

14:18.294 --> 14:21.562
I'm going back for Marshall;
I just need to get some money.

14:21.564 --> 14:24.598
You have nothing to worry about;
these are the "good" mobsters.

14:24.600 --> 14:27.234
Wow, what kind of bozo
does that to a friend?

14:27.236 --> 14:29.854
Shut it, Ralph Macchio!

14:29.856 --> 14:30.938
No, you shut it!

14:30.940 --> 14:34.358
Ralph Macchio's right,
you <i>are</i> a bozo.

14:34.360 --> 14:36.527
Um, I think they prefer
"people of bright color."

14:36.529 --> 14:38.145
You know what
a bachelor party's about?

14:38.147 --> 14:40.664
Hanging out with your friends
and having a good time.

14:40.666 --> 14:43.701
But you only care about
the good time, not the friends.

14:43.703 --> 14:44.818
So you know what?

14:44.820 --> 14:47.004
I'm-I'm done
caring about you then.

14:47.006 --> 14:48.489
I'm out of here.

14:48.491 --> 14:49.790
Ted...

14:51.659 --> 14:53.878
Ted, Ted, I have...

14:53.880 --> 14:56.347
I just tore your mom away
from a living version

14:56.349 --> 14:59.433
of a Nick Nolte mug shot
and put her in a cab home.

14:59.435 --> 15:01.001
Thank you for abandoning me

15:01.003 --> 15:03.771
on what has been one of
the worst nights of my life.

15:03.773 --> 15:06.173
So, it's my usual fee,
plus I always charge

15:06.175 --> 15:08.559
an extra hundred for
girl-on-clown action.

15:08.561 --> 15:10.978
What the hell
is she doing here?

15:10.980 --> 15:13.147
Robin, I swear,
nothing happened.

15:13.149 --> 15:14.899
That means just hand stuff.
(horn honks)

15:14.901 --> 15:17.034
You...!
Oh!

15:17.036 --> 15:20.871
No, no, stop, stop, stop!

15:20.873 --> 15:21.956
Sorry, Barney,

15:21.958 --> 15:25.876
this... this-this is
unforgivable.

15:25.878 --> 15:27.328
It's over.

15:29.548 --> 15:32.082
You know...

15:32.084 --> 15:34.034
I never got to do that.

15:35.887 --> 15:38.038
(sighs)

15:42.060 --> 15:43.644
(sighs)

15:43.646 --> 15:45.212
Ted?

15:45.214 --> 15:47.014
Robin.

15:47.016 --> 15:49.817
We're right on schedule.

15:53.574 --> 15:55.665
Barney is suicidal.
I know, it's awesome!

15:55.666 --> 15:56.721
(both laughing)

15:56.722 --> 15:58.389
NARRATOR:
<i>Yep, kids, we had planned out</i>

15:58.391 --> 15:59.757
<i>every step of the night.</i>

15:59.759 --> 16:01.792
It started three weeks earlier.

16:01.794 --> 16:03.811
...and you will disappoint me.

16:04.813 --> 16:06.931
But make it great, okay?

16:06.933 --> 16:08.983
Oh, it'll be great,
all right!

16:08.985 --> 16:10.868
Okay, after two weeks
of brainstorming,

16:10.870 --> 16:13.320
all I have on my list
so far is Purell.

16:13.322 --> 16:14.855
Marshall, what
do you got?

16:14.857 --> 16:17.107
Well, nothing <i>now.</i>

16:17.109 --> 16:18.626
This is impossible!

16:18.628 --> 16:20.744
How do you make something
memorable for a guy

16:20.746 --> 16:22.997
who makes every night
the best night of his life?

16:22.999 --> 16:26.400
Give him the worst night
of his life.

16:26.402 --> 16:30.371
<i>We'll give him</i>
<i>the worst hotel room</i>

16:30.373 --> 16:32.155
with the worst entertainment,
(horn honks)

16:32.157 --> 16:34.091
<i>the wrong Karate Kid,</i>

16:34.093 --> 16:37.327
and the absolute last stripper
he would want to see.

16:37.329 --> 16:38.512
Hold on.

16:38.514 --> 16:40.764
You want me to pretend
my life's gone to crap

16:40.766 --> 16:43.333
and I'm back to stripping
just screw with my ex-fiancé?

16:44.102 --> 16:45.102
I love it!

16:46.254 --> 16:48.973
That party will be so terrible,
he'll have to leave it.

16:48.975 --> 16:52.676
<i>Then I'll instruct</i>
<i>his arch-nemesis to say...</i>

16:52.678 --> 16:55.029
I mean, what kind of loser
has his bachelor party

16:55.031 --> 16:57.531
ten yards from A.C.
and doesn't even gamble?

16:57.533 --> 16:59.867
ROBIN: <i>Barney will take</i>
<i>the envelope of cash I gave him</i>

16:59.869 --> 17:02.236
<i>and head straight</i>
<i>into our trap.</i>

17:02.238 --> 17:03.387
Hold on.

17:03.389 --> 17:05.489
You want us to rig a casino game

17:05.491 --> 17:07.574
to trick one of
our former high rollers?

17:07.576 --> 17:09.410
Um...

17:09.412 --> 17:10.243
I love it.

17:10.246 --> 17:11.878
Well, then
you get Barney

17:11.881 --> 17:14.196
to use one of these
guys as collateral.

17:14.199 --> 17:15.866
He'll probably choose me.
What?

17:15.867 --> 17:17.217
Well, I'd be worth more.

17:17.219 --> 17:18.935
Yeah. Perfect teeth.

17:18.938 --> 17:20.338
(clears throat)
Yeah, it's just, uh,

17:20.339 --> 17:22.056
just I'm <i>way</i> more athletic
than you.

17:22.058 --> 17:23.390
Yeah, this coming
from the guy

17:23.392 --> 17:25.392
who's never beaten me
at skee-ball.

17:25.394 --> 17:27.511
The only reason a mobster
might choose you is because

17:27.512 --> 17:29.880
they'd be afraid I'd go all
"Marshall Unchained" on them,

17:29.882 --> 17:31.382
which obviously isn't
a risk with you.

17:31.384 --> 17:34.401
Oh, you want to see
some "Ted Unchained," huh?

17:34.403 --> 17:36.236
I'll show you Ted Unchained!

17:37.238 --> 17:38.355
Marshall, would you mind

17:38.357 --> 17:39.890
standing over there
for good luck?

17:39.892 --> 17:41.659
Oh, yeah, sure.

17:45.780 --> 17:47.164
ROBIN:
<i>Meanwhile, I'll make sure</i>

17:47.166 --> 17:50.167
he's abandoned me
in my nightmare scenario.

17:50.169 --> 17:53.454
Hold on. You want me to
help you trick my own son?

17:54.456 --> 17:55.622
I love it.

17:55.624 --> 17:56.507
(sighs)

17:56.509 --> 17:57.508
Barney deserves it.

17:57.510 --> 17:59.710
You know, he told me
you were a virgin.

17:59.712 --> 18:01.462
(scoffs)
Ridiculous!

18:01.464 --> 18:02.513
I know.
(laughs)

18:02.515 --> 18:05.966
You are a dirty ho-bag
just like me.

18:06.685 --> 18:08.251
But he loves you so much.

18:08.253 --> 18:09.303
And so do I.

18:09.305 --> 18:11.755
(mouthing)

18:11.757 --> 18:13.590
Wait, hold on.
Is there any chance

18:13.592 --> 18:16.643
this is all too
mean to Barney?

18:17.645 --> 18:19.697
(laughter)

18:19.699 --> 18:21.331
Just kidding.

18:21.333 --> 18:23.150
Okay, we just need
the finale.

18:23.152 --> 18:25.319
Oh! The Chinese mobsters
chop off my hand

18:25.321 --> 18:26.870
right in front of Barney!

18:27.706 --> 18:29.907
Yes, we're all
equally enthused!

18:32.043 --> 18:34.044
Okay, here's the plan.
After I storm off...

18:34.046 --> 18:35.879
MARSHALL:
Barney!

18:35.881 --> 18:37.965
Barney, hurry!
Give them the money!

18:37.967 --> 18:39.833
Please, hurry!
Oh, no!

18:39.835 --> 18:41.802
The Chinese mobster
is giving Marshall back

18:41.804 --> 18:43.387
and taking me hostage instead,

18:43.389 --> 18:46.123
because he says
I'm obviously more valuable!

18:46.125 --> 18:48.008
Can you, can you
unlock the door?

18:48.010 --> 18:49.059
Barney, please!

18:49.061 --> 18:50.761
They're gonna
chop off my hand!

18:50.763 --> 18:51.795
No, they're not!

18:51.797 --> 18:53.296
They said you're free,
and I think

18:53.298 --> 18:55.399
we agreed that's not
something mobsters would do.

18:55.401 --> 18:57.234
Ted, come on!
This is my thing!

18:57.236 --> 18:58.402
Don't hurt him.

18:58.404 --> 18:59.570
I've got the money.

18:59.572 --> 19:00.988
Too late!

19:00.990 --> 19:02.906
(screaming)

19:03.942 --> 19:06.026
Not my skee-ball hand!

19:06.978 --> 19:08.695
No...!
No...!

19:08.697 --> 19:10.064
No!

19:11.816 --> 19:14.317
Please, just don't shoot me
in the face... or the crotch!

19:14.319 --> 19:16.670
ALL:
Surprise!

19:16.672 --> 19:19.206
What's going on?

19:19.208 --> 19:20.707
Well, we decided to give you

19:20.709 --> 19:23.093
everything you wanted
for your bachelor party

19:23.095 --> 19:25.162
without you even realizing it.

19:26.931 --> 19:29.883
Wait, so that's why you made me
think Marshall might die?

19:31.102 --> 19:33.670
And I'd lost all that money
and my friends hated me

19:33.672 --> 19:35.439
and my wedding was off?

19:35.441 --> 19:36.690
You just decided

19:36.692 --> 19:38.225
to-to check off

19:38.227 --> 19:40.394
everything on this list
in the most

19:40.396 --> 19:42.980
twisted way imaginable?

19:42.982 --> 19:45.365
That is awesome!

19:45.367 --> 19:48.535
And it was all planned
by a girl.

19:48.537 --> 19:49.620
(laughs):
Wow!

19:51.689 --> 19:54.124
So, Lily...

19:54.126 --> 19:56.076
later on tonight,
you want to, um...?

19:56.078 --> 19:58.295
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:58.297 --> 20:00.664
That was all just
part of the act.

20:00.666 --> 20:02.382
Y-You knew that, right?

20:03.218 --> 20:04.802
Yeah! Totally.

20:04.804 --> 20:06.536
We pulled it off, right?

20:06.538 --> 20:08.038
Platonic shake!

20:14.078 --> 20:19.650
Everyone, everyone, thank you
for an incredible bro mitzvah.

20:19.652 --> 20:20.734
Mazel brov!

20:20.736 --> 20:22.552
ALL:
Mazel brov!

20:22.554 --> 20:24.404
(chuckles)

20:24.406 --> 20:26.607
Mm, oh, you didn't really get
everything on the list.

20:26.609 --> 20:27.574
N-No offense

20:27.576 --> 20:28.826
to Ralph Macchio,

20:28.828 --> 20:31.161
but he ain't the Karate Kid.

20:31.163 --> 20:33.113
I couldn't agree
with you more.

20:35.083 --> 20:38.085
You know,
they almost didn't get me.

20:39.838 --> 20:43.790
But after
18 voice mails...

20:43.792 --> 20:46.593
I returned Robin's call.

20:46.595 --> 20:47.961
And she told me

20:47.963 --> 20:50.848
how you're one of the
few people in the world

20:50.850 --> 20:53.100
who truly gets
<i>The Karate Kid</i> movie.

20:54.252 --> 20:57.938
So when she asked if I'd help,

20:57.940 --> 21:00.357
well, my answer
just had to be...

21:02.527 --> 21:04.311
Hai!

21:04.853 --> 21:07.153
William Zabka!
(all cheering)

21:07.155 --> 21:11.255
